ments of political ideals or resistance. The collection also shows how the persistent east/west symbolic border continues to act as a source of these desires in European political and social life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aBoundariesxAnthropological aspectszEurope, Eastern. 0aBoundariesxSocial aspectszEurope, Eastern. 0aSexxPolitical aspectszEurope, Eastern. 0aSexxSocial aspectszEurope, Eastern. 4amanchesterhive variable pricing textbooks. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aBorder crossing.  aBorders and desire.  aEastern borders of Europe.  aEthnosexuality.  aGender and borders.  aNational imaginaries.  aPolitical desires.  aPostsocialism and migration.  aSexualised borders.1 aDavydova-Minguet, Olga, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDiatlova, Anastasia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDimova, Rozita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreen, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHelms, Elissa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHelms, Elissa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKahlina, Katja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLulle, Aija, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNäre, Lena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPulkkinen, Tuija, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPulkkinen, Tuija, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPöllänen, Pirjo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRistivojević, Dušica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchäuble, Michae